+## [2026-07-09T00:00:00Z] tui — `[i] info` legend + full-screen read-only info panel
+
+**Action:** Repurposed the grid-mode `i` binding from the narrow bottom-strip idea preview (`original_text` only) into a full-screen, read-only **info panel**. The panel renders slug, stage, `created_at`, full idea text, working-dir path, latest log path, plus stage-specific extras (`brainstorm.md` in 2-brainstorm, `plan.md` in 3-plan, the latest execute-log tail in 4-execute; 1-inbox and 5–9 show common fields only). The internal mode `:idea_preview` was renamed to `:info`; the message `OpenIdeaPreview` → `OpenInfo`; `Views::IdeaPreview` → `Views::Info`; model fields `idea_preview_text`/`idea_preview_slug` → `Model::InfoState`. The close contract narrowed from "any key dismisses" to `q`/`Esc`/`i` (other keys now NOOP so the panel stays open). A permanent `[i] info` legend chip was added to the footer hint between `[?] help` and `[q] quit` (footer budget bumped 70 → 80 chars; `default_footer` truncates below 80). The `?` help-overlay `i` line and its mode group were updated to stay coherent. No editing, no network, no git ops, no file mutation, no UI-thread blocking (all disk reads live in `BubbleModel#open_info` at keystroke time).
+
+**Refreshed pages:**
+- [[commands/tui]] — footer-layout ASCII, Modes table (renamed Idea preview → Info panel), Keybindings table `i` row.
